        Finance Pre-Approval When Accepting an Offer in Brisbane: A Seller's Guide
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size:1rem;color:rgba(240,236,228,0.6);line-height:1.8;max-width:54ch;">
        A subject-to-finance offer from an unqualified buyer can cost you time, legal fees, and the chance to sell to someone genuinely ready to proceed. Here's what a pre-approval letter actually tells you and how to assess buyer financial strength before saying yes.
      </p>
    </div>
